## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Loop Resource Guard (Compiler Layer)

The `__eden_max_loop_iterations__` global is set to `10,000` in `templates.py:457` but **never referenced in compiled output**. The `render_for`, `render_while`, and `render_recursive` directives in `template_directives.py` emit raw Jinja `{% for %}` loops with no safety net.

#### [MODIFY] [template_directives.py](file:///c:/PROJECTS/eden-framework/eden/template_directives.py)

**`render_for` (line 272-283)**: Wrap the loop body with an iteration counter check. The compiled output changes from:

```diff
-{% for item in items %}...body...{% endfor %}
+{% for item in items %}{% if loop.index0 >= __eden_max_loop_iterations__ %}<!-- EDEN: Loop iteration limit ({{ __eden_max_loop_iterations__ }}) exceeded -->{% break %}{% endif %}...body...{% endfor %}
```

**`render_while` (line 285-290)**: The `while` directive already uses `range(2147483647)` — add the same guard.

**`render_recursive` (line 480-497)**: Add the same guard to recursive loops.

**Design Decision**: Use `{% break %}` + HTML comment rather than raising a Python exception at template render time. This is more forgiving — the page still renders with partial content rather than crashing entirely. The comment is visible in dev tools for debugging.

